# Copy to ".env" in this directory (repo root, next to CYRUS.md).
# The dashboard loads it automatically — no need to export vars in the shell.
#
# --- Billing: pick ONE primary path locally ---
# Console API (metered): uncomment and set:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-...
#
# Claude subscription (Pro / Max) instead: leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY unset, then log in
# once with Claude Code on this machine (e.g. `claude` in a terminal — OAuth / subscription).
# The CLI/SDK reads ~/.claude under your normal HOME. Do not set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in .env
# if you want subscription auth; otherwise the server strips ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN (see docs).
#
# BRAIN_CHAT_BACKEND=sdk
# DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=
# BRAIN_CHAT_MCP_DB=1
#
# --- Multi-user (optional) ---
# When BRAIN_MULTI_USER=1: use SESSION_SECRET (32+ chars) instead of DASHBOARD_PASSWORD for sessions.
# Tenant data lives under DB_DIR (or TENANT_VOLUME_ROOT): registry.db + users/<uuid>/{workspace,data}/.
# Add users: cd app && npm install && cd .. && node scripts/brain-add-user.cjs --login you@x.com --password '…' [--name "Your Name"] [--seed-dbs path/to/folder/with-four-.db]
# Remove a tenant: node scripts/brain-delete-user.cjs --login you@x.com   (preview)   then add --yes to delete registry row + users/<uuid>/
# BRAIN_MULTI_USER=1
# Multi-user chat: disables Claude auto-memory / global CLAUDE.md layers; adds signed-in name from registry to the prompt.
# With ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set, also uses per-tenant HOME under data/.claude-chat-runtime/. Without a key, HOME stays yours so ~/.claude OAuth still works locally.
# Optional: BRAIN_CHAT_LOAD_CLAUDE_MDS=1 — allow project CLAUDE.md layers (default off for tenant isolation).
# SESSION_SECRET=your-random-secret-at-least-32-characters-long
# TENANT_VOLUME_ROOT=/data
# Optional: if markdown trees are not next to DBs, set to the folder that has team/, CYRUS.md, etc.
# LEGACY_WORKSPACE_DIR=/path/to/repo/root
#
# Only if `claude` is not beside your Node binary (see docs/system.md):
# CLAUDE_CODE_EXECUTABLE=/full/path/to/claude
